* D-D-D-D-Down, are you...

39
00:01:17,278 --> 00:01:18,646
(vocalizing)

40
00:01:18,679 --> 00:01:20,248
Ah...

41
00:01:21,782 --> 00:01:24,252
(sighs)
You're an angel.

42
00:01:24,285 --> 00:01:25,653
(Lucifer sighs)

43
00:01:25,686 --> 00:01:27,221
Oh, gosh.

44
00:01:27,255 --> 00:01:28,189
Uh, my apologies.

45
00:01:28,222 --> 00:01:30,391
And for the record,
I don't usually suffer

46
00:01:30,424 --> 00:01:32,826
from premature unfurling.

47
00:01:32,860 --> 00:01:34,395
(grunts, chuckles)

48
00:01:34,428 --> 00:01:37,131
Right.
Now, where were we?

49
00:01:37,165 --> 00:01:39,333
No, keep them out.

50
00:01:39,367 --> 00:01:42,403
I'm totally into cosplay.

51
00:01:42,436 --> 00:01:45,539
I could dress up as a devil
and make it really sexy.

52
00:01:45,573 --> 00:01:50,211
I have no desire
to have sex with myself.

53
00:01:50,244 --> 00:01:52,513
Not right now, at least.

54
00:01:52,546 --> 00:01:53,847
Where are you going?

55
00:01:53,881 --> 00:01:56,250
To do some grooming.

56
00:01:56,284 --> 00:01:59,320
(sighs)

57
00:01:59,353 --> 00:02:00,721
I'd recommend you leave. Now.

58
00:02:02,556 --> 00:02:04,192
I'm about to engage
in a rather gruesome form

59
00:02:04,225 --> 00:02:05,459
of manscaping.

60
00:02:05,493 --> 00:02:06,894
LINDA:
You cut them off, didn't you?

61
00:02:06,927 --> 00:02:09,230
I did, yes.

62
00:02:09,263 --> 00:02:11,365
But then they grew back,
so I cut them off again.

63
00:02:11,399 --> 00:02:12,866
It's like whack-a-mole
back there.

64
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:14,468
(chuckles)

65
00:02:14,502 --> 00:02:15,869
I'm worried about you.

66
00:02:15,903 --> 00:02:19,407
What you're describing
is self-mutilation.

67
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:22,210
Doctor, someone is
forcing those wings on me.

68
00:02:22,243 --> 00:02:24,245
They took away my devil face.

69
00:02:24,278 --> 00:02:26,580
And I won't stand for someone
making me something I'm not.

70
00:02:28,582 --> 00:02:30,718
Are you any closer to
finding out who did this?

71
00:02:30,751 --> 00:02:33,554
Yes. Well, a little.

72
00:02:33,587 --> 00:02:35,956
He calls himself
"The Sinnerman."

73
00:02:35,989 --> 00:02:37,124
From what I can gather,

74
00:02:37,157 --> 00:02:40,294
he's a criminal mastermind
who just moved his operation

75
00:02:40,328 --> 00:02:42,730
to Los Angeles, but no one
seems to have ever met him,

76
00:02:42,763 --> 00:02:45,499
which makes punching him in the
face frustratingly difficult.

77
00:02:45,533 --> 00:02:47,768
Well, maybe... (groans)

78
00:02:47,801 --> 00:02:48,802
Doctor,

79
00:02:48,836 --> 00:02:50,804
are you sure you're all right
to be back at work?

80
00:02:50,838 --> 00:02:52,306
I mean, it really
hasn't been that long

81
00:02:52,340 --> 00:02:53,641
since Mum flambéed you.

82
00:02:53,674 --> 00:02:56,477
Yes. It certainly was a...

83
00:02:56,510 --> 00:02:57,978
traumatic experience.

84
00:02:58,011 --> 00:02:59,913
Fortunately, I'm trained to deal
with that sort of thing,

85
00:02:59,947 --> 00:03:01,315
and I'm doing just that.

86
00:03:01,349 --> 00:03:03,451
And there's nothing
I can do to help?

87
00:03:03,484 --> 00:03:05,753
Yes. You can let me
get back to you.

88
00:03:05,786 --> 00:03:07,921
Oh, if you insist.

89
00:03:07,955 --> 00:03:11,625
Oh, I haven't even told you
the worst part, have I?

90
00:03:11,659 --> 00:03:13,461
Not only did he stick
my wings back on

91
00:03:13,494 --> 00:03:15,863
and take my face,
he's stolen my shtick as well.

92
00:03:17,365 --> 00:03:18,466
He gives out favors to people

93
00:03:18,499 --> 00:03:20,368
for a price to be named later.

94
00:03:20,401 --> 00:03:21,569
Sound familiar?

95
00:03:21,602 --> 00:03:26,307
Lucifer, you didn't invent
the idea of giving out favors.

96
00:03:26,340 --> 00:03:29,310
(chuckles) Yep,
forgot who I was talking to.

97
00:03:29,343 --> 00:03:31,345
I suppose you did.

98
00:03:31,379 --> 00:03:33,547
But you haven't given
out favors in a while.

99
00:03:33,581 --> 00:03:34,982
And the Sinnerman knows it.

100
00:03:35,015 --> 00:03:36,850
I think he's
taunting me.

101
00:03:36,884 --> 00:03:38,352
Do you think he's human?

102
00:03:38,386 --> 00:03:39,787
Or something else?

103
00:03:39,820 --> 00:03:41,622
I don't know.

104
00:03:41,655 --> 00:03:45,025
But whatever he is, I'm gonna
stop at nothing to find him.

105
00:03:45,058 --> 00:03:46,327
CHLOE:
We found him.

106
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:48,329
LUCIFER:
Who? The missing link?

107
00:03:48,362 --> 00:03:50,464
Proof of human-rodent
copulation.

108
00:03:50,498 --> 00:03:51,532
It's Mike Alonso.

109
00:03:51,565 --> 00:03:53,601
The guy that skewered your
kidnapper under the pier.

110
00:03:53,634 --> 00:03:56,036
(scoffs) This is clearly
not the Sinnerman.

111
00:03:56,069 --> 00:03:58,038
Clearly not,
since I'm pretty sure

112
00:03:58,071 --> 00:03:59,907
that no one with that name
actually exists.

113
00:03:59,940 --> 00:04:02,776
He had motive, no alibi,

114
00:04:02,810 --> 00:04:04,878
and, oh, yeah,
he confessed

115
00:04:04,912 --> 00:04:06,780
under interrogation.
He's our guy.

116
00:04:06,814 --> 00:04:08,582
Well, then he must be
working for the Sinnerman.

117
00:04:09,717 --> 00:04:11,051
You're not gonna drag me

118
00:04:11,084 --> 00:04:12,886
into whatever new
weird drama this is.

119
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:14,588
And could you please

120
00:04:14,622 --> 00:04:15,956
stop saying "Sinnerman"?

121
00:04:15,989 --> 00:04:17,425
Sinnerman.

122
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:19,927
Big Nina Simone fan?

123
00:04:19,960 --> 00:04:21,529
Well, actually, I am.
But I was just saying
What? Nothing.

124
00:04:21,562 --> 00:04:22,463
to the detective...
Nothing. It's nothing.

125
00:04:24,465 --> 00:04:26,700
Are you hiding something
from me, Detective?

126
00:04:26,734 --> 00:04:29,637
No.

127
00:04:29,670 --> 00:04:31,339
I don't care;
I was just asking.

128
00:04:31,372 --> 00:04:33,874
New case came in,
you're up.

129
00:04:33,907 --> 00:04:34,942
Thank you.

130
00:04:34,975 --> 00:04:36,143
(sighs)

131
00:04:36,176 --> 00:04:39,079
Okay. Why did you just stop me
telling the new lieutenant

132
00:04:39,112 --> 00:04:40,948
we're on the cusp of the
greatest case of our lives?

133
00:04:40,981 --> 00:04:44,485
Because the Sinnerman is an
urban myth; he doesn't exist.

134
00:04:44,518 --> 00:04:46,320
He's a boogeyman
that criminals use

135
00:04:46,354 --> 00:04:47,555
to hide their bad behavior.

136
00:04:47,588 --> 00:04:49,056
"Oh, the Sinnerman
made me do it."

137
00:04:49,089 --> 00:04:50,624
Yet another thing
he's stolen from me,

138
00:04:50,658 --> 00:04:53,060
being blamed for
the bad deeds of men.

139
00:04:53,093 --> 00:04:55,563
He can keep that one, actually.
(scoffs) So the idea

140
00:04:55,596 --> 00:04:57,898
of telling our new boss--

141
00:04:57,931 --> 00:04:59,967
who I'm just starting
to get a rhythm with--

142
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:02,102
that you want to arrest
the Easter Bunny

143
00:05:02,135 --> 00:05:03,637
doesn't really thrill me.

144
00:05:03,671 --> 00:05:04,772
I have no intention
of arresting anyone.

145
00:05:04,805 --> 00:05:06,774
I want to grab him by his
neck and see what happens

146
00:05:06,807 --> 00:05:08,342
when I squeeze hard enough.

147
00:05:08,376 --> 00:05:12,079
If you can bring me
any tiny bit of evidence

148
00:05:12,112 --> 00:05:13,781
that the Sinnerman
actually exists,

149
00:05:13,814 --> 00:05:15,449
I will be the first
to look into it.

150
00:05:15,483 --> 00:05:17,117
But...

151
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:21,021
until then,
consider this case closed.

152
00:05:21,054 --> 00:05:22,990
And let's focus
on this case, please.

153
00:05:23,023 --> 00:05:24,392
Okay.

154
00:05:24,425 --> 00:05:25,459
* Ah, ah, ah

155
00:05:25,493 --> 00:05:28,128
* Ah-ah, ah, ah, ah-ah
* Come on *

156
