* My eyes see what you got

163
00:05:48,516 --> 00:05:50,984
* I'll get on my knees
and pray *

164
00:05:51,018 --> 00:05:53,120
LUCIFER:
(whistles) Daniel?

165
00:05:53,153 --> 00:05:55,589
Guy's name
is JD Woodstock.

166
00:05:55,623 --> 00:05:57,458
He lived right
around the corner.

167
00:05:57,491 --> 00:05:58,959
Neighbors said he
was pretty quiet.

168
00:05:58,992 --> 00:06:00,628
Unemployed, but we
found this on him.

169
00:06:00,661 --> 00:06:02,430
Huh.

170
00:06:04,665 --> 00:06:05,899
So what are these? Jokes?

171
00:06:05,933 --> 00:06:08,502
A charitable description,
Detective.

172
00:06:08,536 --> 00:06:09,503
"Avocado?

173
00:06:09,537 --> 00:06:11,505
How about avoca-don't?"

174
00:06:11,539 --> 00:06:13,040
Would it be rude
to throw tomatoes at a corpse?

175
00:06:13,073 --> 00:06:14,908
DAN: Looks like he was
a struggling comedian.

176
00:06:14,942 --> 00:06:17,077
We're trying to figure out
if he performed anywhere.

177
00:06:17,110 --> 00:06:18,546
What'd he do? Make
fun of the wrong person?

178
00:06:18,579 --> 00:06:19,880
Get in a fight with
an audience member?

179
00:06:19,913 --> 00:06:21,615
It's worth exploring,
at least.

180
00:06:21,649 --> 00:06:23,484
You know, there are a lot
of insult comics out there,

181
00:06:23,517 --> 00:06:25,453
and not everybody
enjoys being mocked.

182
00:06:25,486 --> 00:06:26,854
Hmm. We should listen
to Daniel, actually.

183
00:06:26,887 --> 00:06:28,589
He's got a unique
insight into this case.

184
00:06:28,622 --> 00:06:30,190
What's he talking about?

185
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:31,592
Well, they're
kindred spirits.

186
00:06:31,625 --> 00:06:33,561
A fellow broken
soul who puts

187
00:06:33,594 --> 00:06:34,862
the most embarrassing parts
of his life on display

188
00:06:34,895 --> 00:06:36,430
for his audience
for an easy laugh.

189
00:06:36,464 --> 00:06:38,632
He does stand-up;
I do improv.

190
00:06:38,666 --> 00:06:39,700
They're completely
different things.

191
00:06:39,733 --> 00:06:40,968
Oh.
Improv

192
00:06:41,001 --> 00:06:42,603
is all about "yes, and."

193
00:06:42,636 --> 00:06:43,904
Stand-up, well, that's about
telling jokes...

194
00:06:43,937 --> 00:06:45,739
I-I regret starting
this entire conversation.

195
00:06:45,773 --> 00:06:47,908
Wait. Excuse me, Dan.

196
00:06:47,941 --> 00:06:48,809
You do improv?

197
00:06:48,842 --> 00:06:51,712
How did I not know that?
And how did he?

198
00:06:51,745 --> 00:06:53,547
Well, it's a funny story,
actually.
Actually,

199
00:06:53,581 --> 00:06:55,082
it's because I-I don't
tell a lot of people.

200
00:06:55,115 --> 00:06:56,049
Why?

201
00:06:56,083 --> 00:06:57,718
Yeah-- hey, Ella.

202
00:06:57,751 --> 00:06:59,553
How's it going?
What'd you find?

203
00:06:59,587 --> 00:07:02,590
Well, no murder weapon, but I
did find three shell casings.

204
00:07:02,623 --> 00:07:04,592
Running ballistics
on them now.

205
00:07:04,625 --> 00:07:07,160
But, based on the
firing pattern,

206
00:07:07,194 --> 00:07:10,664
I think this dude was tortured
before he finally died.

207
00:07:10,698 --> 00:07:12,600
Oh, well congratulations,
Mr. Woodstock.

208
00:07:12,633 --> 00:07:14,668
At least someone cared enough
about your jokes to...

209
00:07:14,702 --> 00:07:15,669
ELLA: Did you just
say Woodstock?

210
00:07:15,703 --> 00:07:18,005
As in, JD Woodstock?

211
00:07:18,038 --> 00:07:19,172
Yeah. Why?
You know him?

212
00:07:19,206 --> 00:07:20,574
Yeah. He made big news
a couple days ago,

213
00:07:20,608 --> 00:07:22,510
claiming Bobby Lowe
stole his jokes.

214
00:07:22,543 --> 00:07:24,612
And who is Bobby Lowe?
A rival comedian

215
00:07:24,645 --> 00:07:26,680
who hates himself so much
he stole this drivel?

216
00:07:26,714 --> 00:07:29,783
Uh, no.

217
00:07:29,817 --> 00:07:31,585
Open your eyes, pal.

218
00:07:31,619 --> 00:07:33,921
Yeah. JD claimed
that Bobby's show

219
00:07:33,954 --> 00:07:35,489
was based on
his own material.

220
00:07:35,523 --> 00:07:36,624
And that he
could prove it.

221
00:07:36,657 --> 00:07:38,158
Which is impossible,

222
00:07:38,191 --> 00:07:40,628
because Bobby Lowe's show
is all about his life.

223
00:07:40,661 --> 00:07:42,596
Wait, so you're saying that
this giant-headed buffoon

224
00:07:42,630 --> 00:07:44,632
stole our poor
victim's ideas?

225
00:07:44,665 --> 00:07:46,834
His life's work
and built a business out of it?

226
00:07:46,867 --> 00:07:49,703
Mm. So now he's a "poor victim."

227
00:07:49,737 --> 00:07:51,572
Look, I know you don't
believe me, Detective,

228
00:07:51,605 --> 00:07:53,273
but I happen to be going through
something quite similar,

229
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:54,775
so if I can't get
my own justice,

230
00:07:54,808 --> 00:07:58,546
I'm gonna get it for
this poor unfunny soul.

231
00:07:58,579 --> 00:08:01,181
Well, I certainly did want you
to focus on this case,

232
00:08:01,214 --> 00:08:02,983
but be careful
what you wish for.

233
00:08:03,016 --> 00:08:05,519
At least the lieutenant
isn't here.

234
00:08:05,553 --> 00:08:08,121
You know, if you keep saying
crazy things around him,

235
00:08:08,155 --> 00:08:09,957
(over microphone):
who knows what he might do.

236
00:08:09,990 --> 00:08:12,292
Right. When have I ever
cared about that, Detective?

237
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:13,961
Ah, that's true.
(chuckles)

238
00:08:13,994 --> 00:08:15,729
(indistinct conversation
continues over microphone)

239
00:08:18,732 --> 00:08:20,701
*

240
00:08:29,242 --> 00:08:30,978
JD:
I sweated over every joke.

241
00:08:31,011 --> 00:08:33,213
Worked my ass off for months.

242
00:08:33,246 --> 00:08:36,283
And Bobby stole it all
like it was nothing.

243
00:08:36,316 --> 00:08:40,654
Created a show
based on my jokes!

244
00:08:40,688 --> 00:08:42,656
Well Bobby, guess what?

245
00:08:42,690 --> 00:08:44,224
I finally found it.

246
00:08:44,257 --> 00:08:46,994
Proof you're a fraud.

247
00:08:47,027 --> 00:08:51,264
And I'm going to show it
to the world.

248
00:08:51,298 --> 00:08:54,334
Well? Which of these boxes
do I click on for the proof?

249
00:08:54,367 --> 00:08:56,704
None. He posted this video
the day before he died.

250
00:08:56,737 --> 00:08:59,072
And we can't find whatever proof
he claimed to have had.

251
00:08:59,106 --> 00:09:01,008
So that's why JD
was tortured,

252
00:09:01,041 --> 00:09:02,876
so the killer could
find and destroy it?

