00:39:31,470 --> 00:39:34,706
I know the Sinnerman had you
skewer Sam under the pier,

1020
00:39:34,740 --> 00:39:36,775
so tell me everything.

1021
00:39:36,808 --> 00:39:38,444
Who the hell's the Sinnerman?

1022
00:39:38,477 --> 00:39:41,079
(laughs)

1023
00:39:41,112 --> 00:39:43,048
Fine.

1024
00:39:43,081 --> 00:39:45,050
Fine. Let's play
a little game, shall we?

1025
00:39:45,083 --> 00:39:46,384
Look at me.

1026
00:39:48,053 --> 00:39:49,788
Tell me.

1027
00:39:49,821 --> 00:39:54,426
Why did you really
desire Sam's death?

1028
00:39:54,460 --> 00:39:57,829
I... didn't want my girl
to sleep with him anymore.

1029
00:40:00,899 --> 00:40:02,133
And?

1030
00:40:02,167 --> 00:40:05,036
And... that's it.

1031
00:40:05,070 --> 00:40:07,038
I got pissed.

1032
00:40:07,072 --> 00:40:09,174
Went medieval on his ass
to send a message.

1033
00:40:09,207 --> 00:40:11,543
No one touches my girl.

1034
00:40:11,577 --> 00:40:13,645
And what about the Sinnerman?

1035
00:40:13,679 --> 00:40:15,781
Man, I have no idea
what you're talking about.

1036
00:40:15,814 --> 00:40:17,616
Oh, you must know.
Come on, Alonso.

1037
00:40:17,649 --> 00:40:19,050
What about the Sinnerman?

1038
00:40:19,084 --> 00:40:20,719
I don't know.

1039
00:40:20,752 --> 00:40:22,588
You must know!

1040
00:40:24,523 --> 00:40:26,592
I don't know
anything... I swear.

1041
00:40:28,760 --> 00:40:31,029
(swallows hard)

1042
00:40:32,163 --> 00:40:33,965
I believe you.

1043
00:40:38,770 --> 00:40:40,806
LUCIFER:
He was telling the truth.

1044
00:40:40,839 --> 00:40:42,608
I mean, maybe

1045
00:40:42,641 --> 00:40:45,210
the Sinnerman manipulated Alonso
without him realizing it.

1046
00:40:45,243 --> 00:40:48,146
Or perhaps he was just
a deranged fellow who felt

1047
00:40:48,179 --> 00:40:50,616
impaling a rival lover to death
was the way to his girl's heart.

1048
00:40:52,183 --> 00:40:54,986
It's a bit old-fashioned,
really.

1049
00:40:56,722 --> 00:40:58,857
Lucifer, I want
to talk about your wings.

1050
00:40:58,890 --> 00:41:01,126
Oh, bloody hell.
They're not out again?!

1051
00:41:01,159 --> 00:41:03,194
So they grew back?

1052
00:41:04,295 --> 00:41:06,998
They did... this morning.

1053
00:41:07,032 --> 00:41:08,934
Sneaky buggers.

1054
00:41:08,967 --> 00:41:11,503
You can't keep doing this
to yourself.
Oh, I agree.

1055
00:41:11,537 --> 00:41:13,772
You do?
Yes.

1056
00:41:13,805 --> 00:41:16,775
It's getting exhausting...
and quite messy.

1057
00:41:16,808 --> 00:41:19,077
No, I need a new solution.

1058
00:41:19,110 --> 00:41:21,847
Maybe I should hire someone
to do it.

1059
00:41:21,880 --> 00:41:24,883
Or maybe your solution is

1060
00:41:24,916 --> 00:41:28,554
to accept that, for now,
you have wings again.

1061
00:41:28,587 --> 00:41:32,157
What, and let Dad win,
or whoever it bloody is?

1062
00:41:32,190 --> 00:41:34,125
I... I don't think so.

1063
00:41:36,161 --> 00:41:39,798
It's easy to let
external factors... define us.

1064
00:41:39,831 --> 00:41:41,232
(clock ticking)

1065
00:41:41,266 --> 00:41:43,201
Especially the traumatic ones.

1066
00:41:44,870 --> 00:41:47,172
But only if we let them.

1067
00:41:50,275 --> 00:41:52,578
We all have itchy butts.

1068
00:41:52,611 --> 00:41:53,945
Excuse me?

1069
00:41:53,979 --> 00:41:55,547
No, it's just something
a woman said to me

1070
00:41:55,581 --> 00:41:56,915
right before
I punched her in the face.

1071
00:41:59,050 --> 00:42:01,086
It's not about the idea.
It's about the execution.

1072
00:42:01,119 --> 00:42:03,154
It's about how I use the wings.

1073
00:42:03,188 --> 00:42:05,757
That's... actually...

1074
00:42:05,791 --> 00:42:07,759
pretty wise.

1075
00:42:07,793 --> 00:42:09,294
Yeah. So I'll just
tuck them away

1076
00:42:09,327 --> 00:42:11,162
and pretend they don't exist.
Less good.

1077
00:42:11,196 --> 00:42:13,098
Someone else is giving favors.
Who cares?

1078
00:42:14,232 --> 00:42:16,201
I'm Lucifer bloody Morningstar!

1079
00:42:16,234 --> 00:42:18,236
I do favors better
than anyone else.

1080
00:42:18,269 --> 00:42:22,040
Amongst other things,
of course.

1081
00:42:22,073 --> 00:42:24,142
Or at least, I used to.

1082
00:42:24,175 --> 00:42:26,277
And I think that maybe...

1083
00:42:28,179 --> 00:42:29,915
...it's about time
I got back in the game.

1084
00:42:29,948 --> 00:42:31,983
*

1085
00:42:33,852 --> 00:42:35,721
* Please me

1086
00:42:35,754 --> 00:42:40,125
* Oh, won't you
ever please me? *

1087
00:42:40,158 --> 00:42:45,230
* You will give me the faith
and I'll bring it on *

1088
00:42:45,263 --> 00:42:48,133
* There's a way
through the storm. *

1089
00:42:55,841 --> 00:42:58,209
Hello.

1090
00:42:59,811 --> 00:43:05,817
So, tell me. What is it
that you truly desire?

